{
  "texts": [
    "After the first iteration (k = 1), each node embedding expressly retains information from its 1-hop neighborhood, which may be accessed via a path in the length graph 1.",
    "After the second iteration (k = 2), each node embedding contains data from its 2-hop neighborhood; generally, after k iterations, each node embedding includes data from its k-hop setting.",
    "The kind of \"information\" this message passes consists of two main parts: structural information about the graph (i.e., degree of nodes, etc.",
    "), and the other is feature-based.In the message-passing mechanism of a neural network, each node has its message stored in the form of feature vectors, and each time, the neighbor updates the information in the form of the feature vector [1].",
    "This process aggregates the information, which means the grey node is connected to the blue node."
  ]
}